text.text: How to Configure emscharts NEMSIS billing Extract?

text: To configure emsCharts to talk to ZOLL Billing, two areas need to be configured: NEMSIS v3 Webservices and Code tables. ZOLL will do the NEMSIS v3 Webservices configuration on your behalf. You need to change the following fields in the Code tables: Chart Summary Setup, Transport Disposition Options, and Custom NEMSIS Setup.
For more information click this : https://help.zollonline.com/billing/Content/Configuring%20the%20Billing%20API/Configuring%20emsCharts.htm

text.text: How to "Change a deposit date on posted transaction?

text: To change a deposit date on a posted transaction, you can use the Payment posting > Change a deposit date on a posted transaction. You can also use the Changing a Deposit Date on a Posted Transaction tool.
For more information click this : https://help.zollonline.com/billing/Content/Videos.htm?wchannelid=m8t21u1viq&wmediaid=tl38fcc0tf

text.text: How can I "Change a deposit date on posted transaction?

text: To change a deposit date on a posted transaction, you can use the Payment posting > Change a deposit date on a posted transaction. You can also use the Changing a Deposit Date on a Posted Transaction tool. To change the deposit date, you can click the Deposit date field, select a date, and then click Save.
For more information click this : https://help.zollonline.com/billing/Content/Videos.htm?wchannelid=m8t21u1viq&wmediaid=tl38fcc0tf

To administer profit centers, you must enable profit centers and define the profit center type. Profit centers can be geographical regions or names for defining groupings or buckets. To begin, you must: 1. Hover over Manage on the Navigation Bar and select Settings. 2. On the Settings page, click the Profit centers tab. 3. Check the 'Enable profit centers' box. 4. Select a profit center type - 'Geographical Zone of Transport Origin' or 'Name'. 5. Click Save.
For more information click this : https://help.zollonline.com/billing/Content/Videos.htm?wchannelid=m8t21u1viq&wmediaid=kf8z7buwn0

Multi-company management (MCM) enables billing service providers to effectively manage billing operations for one or multiple companies. With MCM, it's easy to share data sets such as payers and facilities and work on claims across your client base.
